place.name: DEMBLEBY
place.gazetteerText: DEMBLEBY, a parish in Sleaford district, Lincoln; 5 miles SE of Ancaster r. station, and 7½ E of Grantham. Post town, Osbournby, under Folkingham. Acres, 1, 071. Real property, £1, 462. Pop., 51. Houses, 11. The living is a rectory in the diocese of Lincoln. Value, &212. Patron, T. R. Buckworth, Esq. The church is old. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
